                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4380: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">von Hindenburg</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Hoover</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-07">July 7,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Since the Paris negotiations have now arrived at a conclusion and the one-year
                    moratorium proposed by you has begun, I desire to express the thanks of the
                    German people to you and to the American people. My most sincere wish is that
                    owing to your initiative the whole world may be led into a new era of peaceful
                    and confident cooperation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Von Hindenburg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
